  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Early Warning and Rapid Response in the Northern Border of Ecuador</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through this project, IOM contributes to positioning IOM&#x2019;s population of interest in the priorities of the national and local governments in Ecuador as a prioritized population with high rates of vulnerability at the northern border, where the former FARC guerrillas were present. In this capacity building process, IOM supports the Ecuadorian Ombudsman Offices in developing an early warning and response system reform within its migration specific mandate.</narrative>
  </description>
